						<summary>

						<p>Above the empty <hi rend="italic">dēvakōshṭhas</hi> on the walls of the outer <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> of the Airāvatēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>These small label inscriptions assignable to about the 12th Century contain the names of the gods and goddesses whose images have been installed therein.</p>						

